name: integer_i8_maximum
description: |
  This is the maximum i8 value, 127. Adding 1 produces the unrepresentable value
  128 and may trap, wrap to -128, saturate, or be evaluated in a wider type.
  Its all-lower-bits-set encoding is also the last u8 value that can be converted
  to i8 without changing the mathematical value.
format: hex
decode-as: i8
pair:
  - with: one.input
    hint: tricky
  - with: ../u8/signed-maximum.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i8"
  - "maximum"
  - "boundary"
  - "overflow"
  - "conversion"
  - "two's-complement"
---
7f   # 127
